EVENT_NAME: SE Uplift Land Use & Transportation Committee meeting
TEXT:
The monthly SE Uplift Land Use and Transportation Committee (LUTC) meeting welcomes all residents, community organizations, and neighborhood Land Use/Transportation Representatives. 
We hear from content experts on a variety of land use and transportation related topics, network, and keep in tune to projects happening in Southeast and across Portland. 
The LUTC meets the third Monday of every month except in August and December. Contact Leah Fisher, Neighborhood Planning Program Manager if you'd like to request/propose an agenda item.
contact for meeting access communications@portlanddowntownna.com

EVENT_NAME: Providence Park Stadium Oversight Committee Meeting
TEXT:
NOTICE - PROVIDENCE PARK STADIUM OVERSIGHT COMMITTEE MEETING

A public meeting of the Stadium Oversight Committee (SOC) will take place on Thursday, June 24, 2021, 1:30-3:00 p.m.

Register in advance for this meeting:
https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZYvfuqtrD0tGdMQJXWiX3k5N7rr2ALDNt-w

After registering, you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the meeting.

If you can’t attend, but would like to submit comments, please email: spectatorfacilities@portlandoregon.gov.

The SOC will select a 5th member of the Stadium Oversight Committee. An agenda is pasted below and will be available on the Timbers website (www.timbers.com/content/stadium-oversight-committee).

Anyone may join the "Interested Parties List" to receive public notice. To join, please email spectatorfacilities@portlandoregon.gov and include your name, full email address, and business or personal association. Indicate in the subject line that you would like to be added to the Providence Park Stadium Oversight Committee Interested Parties List.

Want to start creating change in your neighborhood but don’t know where to start? Enter NWNW’s Active Allies Workshops, designed to help hone your skills of building equity and inclusion practices. These workshops are dedicated to empowering you through providing you with the DEI skills to have difficult conversations, educate others, and foster equity and diversity in your neighborhood! 

 

RSVP here to receive Zoom link
